  &lt;Comment&gt;
    &lt;Title&gt;Kind staff under difficult circumstances&lt;/Title&gt;
    &lt;ScreenName&gt;Naomi Evans&lt;/ScreenName&gt;
    &lt;CommentText&gt;Last night I had to go to A&amp;amp;E, and given the difficult situation the country is in I thought the service would be stretched and maybe struggling to provide usual levels of care. I was wrong - the levels of compassion, kindness and care from the Doctors and staff I spoke with even in the middle of the night at the weekend I found to be very moving given the immense pressure they are under. I was in there because I’d been a bit of an idiot, but my Doctor took the time to really listen and care for me even though it was busy, and even though I was scared and had to be on my own due to current restrictions they made me feel really safe and put me at ease.

I’ve used a lot of different health services all over the country, and am not normally the kind of person to leave a review, but I really wanted to thank the staff for the fantastic job that they’re doing even when things are so tough. You made someone who normally feels very anxious in a hospital environment at the best of times feel safe - thank you.&lt;/CommentText&gt;
